ldc-ALR-Index-ed.def: Adult literacy rate is the percentage of people ages 15 and above who can both read and write with understanding a short simple statement about their everyday life.
ldc-ALR-Index-ed.name: Adult literacy rate

ldc-ALR-Value-ed.def: Adult literacy rate is the percentage of people ages 15 and above who can both read and write with understanding a short simple statement about their everyday life.
ldc-ALR-Value-ed.name: Adult literacy rate

ldc-GPIS-Index-ed.def: Gender parity index for gross enrollment ratio in secondary education is the ratio of girls to boys enrolled at secondary level in public and private schools.
ldc-GPIS-Index-ed.name: Gender parity index for gross secondary school enrollment

ldc-GPIS-Value-ed.def: Gender parity index for gross enrollment ratio in secondary education is the ratio of girls to boys enrolled at secondary level in public and private schools.
ldc-GPIS-Value-ed.name: Gender parity index for gross secondary school enrollment

ldc-GSSE-Index-ed.def: Gross enrollment ratio is the ratio of total enrollment, regardless of age, to the population of the age group that officially corresponds to the level of education shown. Secondary education completes the provision of basic education that began at the primary level, and aims at laying the foundations for lifelong learning and human development, by offering more subject- or skill-oriented instruction using more specialized teachers.
ldc-GSSE-Index-ed.name: Gross secondary school enrollment ratio

ldc-GSSE-Value-ed.def: Gross enrollment ratio is the ratio of total enrollment, regardless of age, to the population of the age group that officially corresponds to the level of education shown. Secondary education completes the provision of basic education that began at the primary level, and aims at laying the foundations for lifelong learning and human development, by offering more subject- or skill-oriented instruction using more specialized teachers.
ldc-GSSE-Value-ed.name: Gross secondary school enrolment ratio

ldc-MMR-Index-ed.def: Maternal mortality ratio is the number of women who die from pregnancy-related causes while pregnant or within 42 days of pregnancy termination. The data are estimated with a regression model using information on the proportion of maternal deaths among non-AIDS deaths in women ages 15-49, fertility, birth attendants, and GDP measured using purchasing power parities (PPPs).
ldc-MMR-Index-ed.name: Maternal mortality rate
ldc-MMR-Index-ed.source: United Nations Maternal Mortality Estimation Inter-Agency Group

ldc-MMR-Value-ed.def: Maternal mortality ratio is the number of women who die from pregnancy-related causes while pregnant or within 42 days of pregnancy termination. The data are estimated with a regression model using information on the proportion of maternal deaths among non-AIDS deaths in women ages 15-49, fertility, birth attendants, and GDP measured using purchasing power parities (PPPs).
ldc-MMR-Value-ed.name: Maternal mortality rate
ldc-MMR-Value-ed.source: United Nations Maternal Mortality Estimation Inter-Agency Group

ldc-STU-Index-ed.def: Prevalence of stunting is the percentage of children under age 5 whose height for age is more than two standard deviations below the median for the international reference population ages 0-59 months. For children up to two years old height is measured by recumbent length. For older children height is measured by stature while standing.
ldc-STU-Index-ed.name: Prevalence of stunting
ldc-STU-Index-ed.source: UNICEF/WHO/World Bank Joint Child Malnutrition Estimates Expanded Database

ldc-STU-Value-ed.def: Prevalence of stunting is the percentage of children under age 5 whose height for age is more than two standard deviations below the median for the international reference population ages 0-59 months. For children up to two years old height is measured by recumbent length. For older children height is measured by stature while standing.
ldc-STU-Value-ed.name: Prevalence of stunting
ldc-STU-Value-ed.source: UNICEF/WHO/World Bank Joint Child Malnutrition Estimates Expanded Database

ldc-U5M-Index-ed.def: Under-five mortality rate is the probability that a newborn baby will die before reaching age five, if subject to age-specific mortality rates of the specified year.
ldc-U5M-Index-ed.name: Under-five mortality rate
ldc-U5M-Index-ed.source: United Nations Interagency Group on Child Mortality Estimation

ldc-U5M-Value-ed.def: Under-five mortality rate is the probability that a newborn baby will die before reaching age five, if subject to age-specific mortality rates of the specified year.
ldc-U5M-Value-ed.name: Under-five mortality rate
ldc-U5M-Value-ed.source: United Nations Interagency Group on Child Mortality Estimation
